geneVariantDescriptions.description: TPM3-NTRK1 results from the fusion of TPM3 and NTRK1, and leads constitutive Trka kinase activity resulting in increased cell growth and tumorigenesis (PMID: 24962792, PMID: 28751539), and leads to cell transformation in culture and activation of MAPK signaling in a reporter assay (PMID: 30279230). TPM3-NTRK1 has been identified in colorectal cancer, including MSI-high colorectal cancer (PMID: 24962792, PMID: 30279230).

references.title: The TPM3-NTRK1 rearrangement is a recurring event in colorectal carcinoma and is associated with tumor sensitivity to TRKA kinase inhibition.
